physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and oriented, no acute distress; HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist; Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/gallops/rubs; Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes/rales/rhonchi; Abdomen: Soft, nondistended, appropriately tender; Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused, 3+ pulses bilaterally; Neurologic: Grossly intact; Psychiatric: Appropriate mood/affect.
